    "created_at": "2015-11-23T06:38:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-23T06:38:31Z",
    "body": "> Until recently, Electron's notifications were just the standard \"Web notifications\" from Chromium. \n\nNope, they've always been native. On OS X, we support most of the features except for the ones described above, because the HTML5 Notification class doesn't natively support it, so being able to reply means we've got to completely ditch Chromium's support for the `Notification` class and recreate our own. There are enough of these kinds of features popping up that this might be Worth It, but right now, we don't\n"
  },
