    "body": "Ahh gotcha - that makes sense. When I saw it was the Chromium web Notification API I figured it came for free in Chromium. 👍 \n\n> On Nov 22, 2015, at 10:39 PM, Paul Betts notifications@github.com wrote:\n> \n> Until recently, Electron's notifications were just the standard \"Web notifications\" from Chromium.\n> \n> Nope, they've always been native. On OS X, we support most of the features except for the ones described above, because the HTML5 Notification class doesn't natively support it, so being able to reply means we've got to completely ditch Chromium's support for the Notification class and recreate our own. There are enough of these kinds of features popping up that this might be Worth It, but right now, we don't\n> \n> —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub.\n"
